      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(logging): prune non-idle stale diagnostic session states",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen `requestStuckSessionRecovery()` fails with `status: \"failed\"`, the diagnostic session state stays non-idle forever because `recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState()` returns `false` and `applyRecoveryOutcomeToDiagnosticState()` returns early without transitioning the entry to `\"idle\"`. The entry accumulates as a ghost in the `diagnosticSessionStates` Map indefinitely.\n\nThis PR transitions **only** `status: \"failed\"` recovery outcomes to idle with `queueDepth = 0`, so the existing stale-idle prune logic can remove them naturally. Other non-mutating outcomes (`noop` with reason `\"skipped\"` or `\"already_in_flight\"`) are **preserved** — their sessions may still be active.\n\nFixes #91697\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/logging/diagnostic-session-recovery-coordinator.ts`**: In `applyRecoveryOutcomeToDiagnosticState()`, when `outcome.status === \"failed\"`, transition the diagnostic entry to `\"idle\"` with `queueDepth = 0`. Other non-mutating outcomes are unaffected. 1 file, +6 lines.\n- **`src/logging/diagnostic-session-state.ts`**: (no changes — prune logic unchanged, reverted v1/v2 fallback)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Failed stuck-session recovery leaves diagnostic entries permanently non-idle. After the fix, only `status: \"failed\"` outcomes trigger the idle transition; skipped and in-flight recoveries preserve their state.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node v22.22.0, Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64, openclaw commit dad3a9dba9. tsx v4.22.3.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n1. Wrote proof script at `scripts/proof-91721-v4.mjs` that imports the real `diagnosticSessionStates`, `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates`, `getDiagnosticSessionState`, `peekDiagnosticSessionState`, and `recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState`\n2. Script creates 4 diagnostic entries, applies 3 recovery outcomes (`failed`, `skipped`, `already_in_flight`), simulates the narrowed coordinator logic, then runs prune\n3. Ran `npx tsx scripts/proof-91721-v4.mjs`\n\n**Evidence after fix (terminal capture):**\n\n```\n$ npx tsx scripts/proof-91721-v4.mjs\n\n============================================================\nrecovery-path ghost state — narrowed fix proof\n============================================================\nnow  = 2026-06-10T12:00:00.000Z\nTTL  = 30 minutes\n\n--- Simulating recovery outcomes ---\n\nCase 1: status=\"failed\"\n  recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState = false\n  status === \"failed\" → ghost-idle transition\n  before: state=processing\n  after:  state=idle queueDepth=0\n\nCase 2: status=\"noop\", reason=\"skipped\"\n  recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState = false\n  status !== \"failed\" → state PRESERVED\n  before: state=processing\n  after:  state=processing (unchanged)\n\nCase 3: status=\"noop\", reason=\"already_in_flight\"\n  recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState = false\n  status !== \"failed\" → state PRESERVED\n  before: state=waiting\n  after:  state=waiting (unchanged)\n\n--- After prune ---\nentries remaining: 3\n\n--- Verification ---\nfailed → idle transition             ✓\nfailed → pruned (ghost gone)         ✓\nskipped state preserved              ✓\nskipped entry still present          ✓\nin-flight state preserved            ✓\nin-flight entry still present        ✓\nfresh entry preserved                ✓\n\n✓ All checks passed.\nghost entries: 0 (failed-recovery cleaned up)\nactive entries: 3 (skipped + in-flight + fresh preserved)\nexit code: 0\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** 4 entries → `failed` transitions to idle and is pruned (ghost gone). `skipped` and `already_in_flight` preserve their original non-idle state (processing/waiting) — their sessions may still be active. `fresh` entry within TTL is untouched. The `status === \"failed\"` gate ensures only proven ghost states are cleaned up.\n\n**What was not tested:** Full gateway restart with stuck-session recovery, heartbeat-driven stuck-session detection, the `scheduleOrphanRecovery` path.",
        "branch": "fix/91697-prune-non-idle-diagnostic-states",
